</para>
<para id="element-18">
Hence, option (d) is correct.
</para>
<para id="element-17">
<note id="idp90592">Important to note here is that this distribution of kinetic energy between translation and rotation is independent of the path of rolling. It only depends on the MI of rolling body i.e. on mass and its distribution about the axis of rotation. As such, the distribution of kinetic energy between translation and rotation are different for different bodies. In the case of ring and hollow cylinder, the distribution is 50% - 50%.</note>
</para>

</solution>
